# Comprehensive Debt Management System — Implementation Plan

This document details the architecture and implementation strategy for integrating a premium Debt Management System directly into the Financial OS.

## Goal Description
The objective is to provide a central hub to manage liabilities, loans, money lent/borrowed, and repayment strategies. The system will shift the experience from stressful debt tracking to an actionable, gamified, and highly visual financial planning experience (including Snowball/Avalanche strategies, EMI calendars, and health scores).

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Database Migrations**
> Modifying the `DebtType` Enum (to add `vehicle_loan`, `education_loan`, `bnpl`, etc.) and adding new fields (`start_date`, `end_date`) to the `debts` table requires altering the existing database schema. Since we are using SQLite for development without a strict Alembic migration history yet, I will use SQLAlchemy's tools or write a quick migration script to alter the tables safely.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **AI Architecture Readiness**
> I will structure the data layer and state management to easily inject future AI insights (e.g., `ai_recommendations` arrays in the API response schema) without implementing the actual LLM calls at this stage.

